snippet.textDisplay: There are a lot of easter eggs in this trailer for the fans of the original, I am wondering just how much of what was in the original, Gozer for example, will reappear.  Jeremy is saying how different this will be, but other than the kids (which I hate, why did they have to do a bloody kids movie version!) I wonder how different it will really be.  We see what looks like a Terror Dog's claw on the hood of that car, we see the familiar green light that signifies a ghost in the original, we see a sign saying Shandor Mining (I am assuming the same Ivo Shandor from the original movie who built Dana's apartment building and formed the Gozer Worshippers?), we have the equipment from the original movie.  Yes, a fan movie I can see, definitely, but if every ghost apocalypse is connected to Shandor where do they go when they defeat him again here?  They could of, and to my mind should of, got a new team of adult Ghostbusters to pass the torch to and figured out a fresh way to get them ghosts to fight rather than obviously leaning heavily on nostalgia and a previous movies plot.

snippet.textDisplay:
Didn't the Ecto-1 in the cartoon or the Ecto-1 toy have a gunner seat too? I kinda remember something like that. If my memory serves me correct, then that little detail is a wonderful little piece of fan service.

But yeah, how could a chunk of the world forget about the Ghostbusters fighting Gozer or Vigo? It's only been a few decades. I'm sure parents still tell their kids and clearly, video exists in this world they've created. And I know we'll reach a historical point where even something like 9/11 will be regarded in a similar sense of "a thing that happened a long time ago", but I feel like more time needs to pass for that than just a couple decades.
